Name: CIFC Corp
Description: DELISTED - CIFC Corp. (CIFC), formerly CIFC Deerfield Corp., is a corporate loan asset managers. As of September 30, 2011, CIFC managed $10.7 billion across 29 collateralized loan obligations (CLOs) and served more than 200 institutional investors in North America, Europe, Asia and Australia. CIFC conducts asset management activities through four principal subsidiaries: CIFC Asset Management LLC, Deerfield Capital Management LLC, CypressTree Investment Management, LLC and Columbus Nova Credit Investments Management LLC. CIFC was formed by the merger of Commercial Industrial Finance Corp. and Deerfield Capital Corp. on April 13, 2011. In February 2012, the Company's wholly owned indirect subsidiaries, DFR Middle Market Holdings Ltd. and Deerfield Capital Management LLC, completed the sale of certain non-core assets.
